Summary

- The moisture streaming into northern CA will shift north Tuesday bringing some lighter snow and more shadowing. Then Tuesday night into Wednesday morning heavy snow pushes back in. The snow should back off again on Wednesday afternoon and evening, then the final wave of heavier snow moves in later Wednesday night into Thursday morning, with scattered snow showers Thursday before the storm ends.
